Hendr JacobsRetired nurse Kitty Erasmus addresses the nurses of the Postmasburg Hospital. Photo: Hendre Jacobs Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Legendary and retired nurses of the Postmasburg Hospital made this year s International Nurses Day celebration special by joining the staff of the hospital and gracing it with their presence on Friday, 12 May. The celebration was held in the form of a lunch where the role of nurses, who form the backbone of the public health system, was recognised.International Nurses Day is celebrated annually on Florence Nightingale s birthday and is a day during which nurses across the world are appreciated for their dedication to their patients.Nurses are seldom recognised for their tireless efforts toward improving the health of society. A retired nurse, Kitty Erasmus, delivered a motivational speech in which she shared funny anecdotes from her 42-year nursing career. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.